Laparoscopic surgery of the pancreas. Diagnostic laparoscopy provides useful information in patients with pancreatic disease and is the most reliable technique for the staging of patients with pancreatic cancer. The advent of laparoscopic contact ultrasonography has enhanced the diagnostic and staging potential of laparoscopy. In addition to laparoscopic cholecystectomy for acute gallstone-associated pancreatitis, the following operations have been performed laparoscopically: bilio-enteric bypass and gastrojejunostomy in patients with advanced pancreatic cancer internal drainage for pseudocysts